               <msContents>
                  <summary> This manuscript is comprised of four works, the Testament of Abraham,
                     Testament of Isaac, Testament of Jacob (ገድለ ፡ አብርሃም, ገድለ ፡ ይስሐቅ, ገድለ ፡ ያዕቆብ), and a homily attributed to Ephrem on
                     Abraham and Sarah in Egypt (ድርሳነ ፡ ሳራ), which in the Ethiopian tradition is almost always
                     circulate together as a unit. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="5r" to="19v">ff. 5r-19v</locus>
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1412GadlaA">Gädlä Abrǝham</title>
                     <note>
                        <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/work_11506">See in FIHRIST.</ref>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl type="relations">
                        <bibl/>
                        <relation name="skos:broadMatch" ref="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broadMatch" active="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/work_11506" passive="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1412GadlaA"/>
                     </listBibl>
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1412GadlaA">Testament of Abraham</title>
                     <note>
                        <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/work_11506">See in FIHRIST.</ref>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl type="relations">
                        <bibl/>
                        <relation name="skos:broadMatch" ref="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broadMatch" active="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/work_11506" passive="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1412GadlaA"/>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Geez</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <locus from="20r" to="34r">ff. 20r-34r</locus>
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1517GadlaY"> Testament of Isaac</title>
                     <note>
                        <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/work_11507">See in FIHRIST.</ref>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl type="relations">
                        <bibl/>
                        <relation name="skos:broadMatch" ref="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broadMatch" active="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/work_11507" passive="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1517GadlaY"/>
                     </listBibl>
                     <note>
                        <locus from="34r" to="34r">f. 34r</locus> End of the testament of Isaac with
                        the addition of a 5-line invocation by a different hand at the
                        bottom.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Geez</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                     <locus from="34v" to="35r">ff. 34v-44v</locus>
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1510GadlaY">Testament of Jacob</title>
                     <note>
                        <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/work_11508">See in FIHRIST.</ref>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl type="relations">
                        <bibl/>
                        <relation name="skos:broadMatch" ref="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broadMatch" active="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/work_11508" passive="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1510GadlaY"/>
                     </listBibl>
                     <note>
                        <locus from="34r" to="43v">ff. 34r-43v</locus> End of the Testament of Jacob
                        on f. <locus from="44r" to="44v">44r-44v</locus>. Invocations on f. <locus from="44v" to="44v">44v</locus> as on f. <locus from="34r" to="34r">34r</locus>. </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Geez</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                     <locus from="44v" to="55r">ff. 44v-55r</locus>
                     <title> Homily of St. Ephrem on
                        Abraham and Sarah in Egypt</title>
                     
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Geez</textLang>
                  </msItem>
